      "series_name": "3M Conformable Bonding Tape",
      "brand_name": "3M",
      "category_name": "",
      "product_description": "Offers very good adhesion performance and high flexibility. Specially designed for rough or highly irregular surfaces, providing strong adhesion for automotive wire harness assembly and excellent conformability for sealing applications. Offers reduced VOCs compared to conventional products.",
      "product_features": "Excellent initial adhesion and static performance on uneven substrates\nHighly conformable tape for sealing and bonding to rough or irregular surfaces\nDemonstrates good visibility due to its light blue color\nExcellent adhesion performance with weather resistance, heat resistance, and chemical resistance\nCan be applied to various substrates used for automotive parts without special surface treatment",
      "main_applications": "Sealing support for various interior part attachments\nSealing support for various exterior part attachments\nBonding support for various interior part attachments\nBonding support for various exterior part attachments\nFixing wire harnesses to the headliner",
      "special_applications": "Automotive wire harness assembly\nSealing on rough or highly irregular surfaces\nDepending on the material (e.g., EPDM rubber), 3M Adhesion Promoter may be required. Please check before use.\nConstruction appears to be paper liner / acrylic pressure sensitive adhesive / non-woven cloth / acrylic pressure sensitive adhesive. Stated total thickness excludes liner thickness.\nTypical performance values are reference data only, not specification limits. Peel and shear values depend on substrate characteristics and/or paint composition. Test reports are available upon request.\nShelf life is three years (36 months) from date of manufacture when stored at 23°C and 50% relative humidity.",
